      "text": "In a case presented in the outpatient department (OPD), a patient reported experiencing abdominal pain and diarrhea. Upon further examination, the patient exhibited symptoms of cutaneous flushing, extensive wheezing, and tricuspid insufficiency. Subsequent contrast enhanced MRI scans indicated the presence of endocardial fibrosis. As a result of this condition, which substance is likely to be excreted excessively by the patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Vanillylmandelic acid"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Imidazoleacetic acid"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "5-hydroxy indole acetic acid"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Choline"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 2,
      "solution": "<ul>\n\t<li>Nowadays, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2eaab075f416927771834adb276f1d\">carcinoid</span> tumor <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"17cd3771bb1692777190950c142dbe\">incidence</span> is rising. The major clinical symptoms include flushing, diarrhea, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9bde62b1091692777183cd433d9d47\">bronchospasm</span> as well as <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2eaab075f416927771834adb276f1d\">carcinoid</span> heart disease. Expression of its <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"38c81721001692777181c671bce8b3\">amine</span> or hormones is variable, so it makes diagnosis of disease late or erroneous. 5-Hydroxy indoleacetic acid (5-HIAA) is considered as important biomarkers for the disease, while <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6fe814334116927771846a84f0e9d8\">Chromogranin</span> A(CgA), <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5bb660d1021692777194ef83e87d22\">pancreatic polypeptide</span> are also used as non-specific biomarkers for the disease.</li>\n\t<li>Primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d92cbff33316927771927b4de10a5b\">metabolic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"385d52533a169277719991c090c3d7\">substrate</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"06eba971ce169277719884f8c62937\">serotonin</span> is 5-Hydroxy indoleacetic acid (5-HIAA). <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"06eba971ce169277719884f8c62937\">Serotonin</span>  gets broken into 5-hydroxy indoleacetic acid (5-HIAA) within the liver.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Incorrect Choices:</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>a. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"d6a30cc0d11692777193e25a043a08\">Neuroblastoma</span> are diagnosed by the presence of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0b72f5e96b16927772018dec8a87e2\">urinary</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"430f3c1a8b16927772018d807e714f\">vanillylmandelic acid</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a01d4c35441692777189c91ae9ac7d\">homo</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"14fcf77cf21692777201a19b874279\">vanillic acid</span> (HVA) as biomarkers. </li>\n\t<li>b.   Breast tumors are caused by imidazole-acetic acid and its derivatives. </li>\n\t<li>d. Dietary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6cdcd39cf2169277719068e247e38d\">intake</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ad6984dc581692777184936c84dd97\">choline</span> in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7a1ae24f701692777187a7f60bbd9f\">excess</span> can cause risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0fce15e71f1692777184feb9af5303\">colon</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9b9c4c412f1692777197ed217e7373\">rectum</span> cancer.<br />\n\t </li>\n</ul>",
