    {
      "text": "The best method for the detection of mutations with low allele frequency is:",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Droplet digital PCR"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "FISH"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Nested PCR"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Sanger sequencing"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A - <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"33843a1c3716927771867f807275d2\">Droplet</span> digital PCR</strong></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Droplet Digital PCR (ddPCR) is a highly sensitive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ef5cb829b8169277719603304e73cb\">quantitative</span> technique</strong> for detecting mutations with very low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88c5dcbf0a1692777181e199712f81\">allele</span> frequencies.</p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>It partitions a sample into thousands of droplets, each containing a single DNA molecule.</li>\n\t<li>PCR is performed on each droplet, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"df068e6efc16927772029693b5023e\">fluorescent</span> probes detect the presence or absence of the mutation.</li>\n\t<li>Specialized equipment analyzes the droplets to count <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"df068e6efc16927772029693b5023e\">fluorescent</span> signals, determining <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7a67bdf6f81692777193cfd480f228\">mutation</span> frequency.</li>\n\t<li>ddPCR is highly accurate and valuable for detecting low-frequency mutations in clinical samples.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<figure class=\"caption_element\"><img alt=\"PCR\" data-author=\"Casmil, Irafasha & Huang, Cynthia & Blakney, Anna. \" data-hash=\"12410\" data-license=\"CC BY 4.0\" data-source=\"https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Assessment-of-PCR-efficiency-using-a-qPCR-platform-a-Map-of-the-saRNA-fLuc-vector-and_fig1_375284435\" data-tags=\"May2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/h7hdrOm2Mv1QMqrKtDS11746698736.png\" />\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n\n<p><strong>Learning Objective:</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Assay Type</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Advantages</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Main Limitations</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Real-time PCR</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Rapid results</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Cost effectiveness</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Limited number of DNA sequences</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Digital <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"33843a1c3716927771867f807275d2\">droplet</span> PCR</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>High sensitivity (detection of low <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88c5dcbf0a1692777181e199712f81\">allele</span> frequency,0.005-0.1)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Limited number of DNA sequences</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Next-generation sequencing</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Larger number of DNA sequences.</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Detection of coexisting mutations.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Higher <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"88c5dcbf0a1692777181e199712f81\">allele</span> frequency required compared to ddPCR (0.1%).</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Higher costs</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>More complex data analysis and interpretation.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p> </p>",
